name: Tre Ban
description: Using the LoverBeer recipe inspired to spontaneous fermentation, this beer is fermented thanks to an inoculum of lactic bacteria and yeasts (including Brettanomyces). 24 months of maturation in Cognac barrels. Refermentation in bottle or keg.

name: Binde
description: Brown Flemish ale inspired, 30 months aged with brettanomyces. Binde is nickname of our niece Matilde. She drew the label. The name refers to Matilde di Canossa whose history is joined to the famous Orval Monastery.

name: Orchard Saison
description: Tart bretty wine barrel aged saison made with organic apple juice from Skåne.

name: Edmund Backhouse Pilsner 北京隐士
After Sauna
description: Collaboration Beer con Sleeping Village (Norway). Prodotta con il 100% di orzo coltivato da noi e maltato a Bamberga.

name: Hazelnut Take Me Home
description: Imperial Stout, da 11% vol., una con aggiunta di nocciole tostate, caratterizzata da un corpo pieno, denso e mouthfeel cremoso. TAKE ME HOME, è la “traduzione” in inglese di ciò che in Veneto è il cosiddetto “para casa” cioè l’ultima birra, quella birra che, di fatto, ti porta a casa.

name: Cocoa Take Me Home
description: Imperial Stout, da 11% vol., una con aggiunta di fave di cacao tostate, caratterizzata da un corpo pieno, denso e mouthfeel cremoso. TAKE ME HOME, è la “traduzione” in inglese di ciò che in Veneto è il cosiddetto “para casa” cioè l’ultima birra, quella birra che, di fatto, ti porta a casa.

name: Letra Craft Trials Tropical Berliner Weisse BA
Azores Juicy IPA
description: The discovery of Azores is also in the sip of this Juicy IPA. A blond beer with the addition of Azores pineapple and balanced with the addition of  the american hops Cascade, Citra, Mosaic and Summit. This beer was inspired by the beautiful landscapes of Azores.

name: Letra On Oak Barrel Aged Oatmeal Stout
description: This Oatmeal Stout has  a black colour, high body and creamy and golden foam. In first plan whisky, coffee and toast notes. Follows the perception of dark chocolate, vanilla and wood. A barrel aged beer with addition of Scotch whisky but easy to drink and discover its sensory characteristics.

name: Inner Circle
description: A Pale Ale brewed with Citra, Mosaic & Simcoe.

name: Surf N Turf
description: Cerveza turbia y cargada de Dry hop de Vic secret.

name: Birds of A Feather
description: A New England-Style IPA brewed and double dry-hopped with juicy American hops. Birds has become a staple of our roster because of its fruit-forward flavors of dank citrus and passionfruit, coupled with a smooth finish and creamy mouthfeel.

name: Barley Smalls
description: A full-bodied Vienna-style lager. The hefty addition of Vienna malts in this beer lend flavors of caramel and toast, while the beer’s slumber under colder temperatures smooths out its bite. This is an easy drinking lager, perfect for sipping in the company of family and friends. Brewed and named in honor or our resident pup.

name: Rabbit Rabbit
description: A dangerously drinkable double dry-hopped Double IPA brewed with fruity and flavorful hops. This beer is a veritable juice bomb, boasting bold flavors of mango, melon, and ripe pineapple, all balanced by a velvety mouthfeel and smooth finish.

name: BeerBrugna
description:
This beer is inocculated by wild yeasts (Brettanomyces included) and lactic bacteria. Small, dark and very sweet Damaschine variety plums, also called Ramassin in Piemontese dialect, are added in steeping to restart a new fermentation to characterize the product.

BeerBrugna is matured in oak barrels (3hl or 5hl capacity) for twelve months.

"The unique use of Damaschine plums gives to this extraordinary beer a lot of warm and sensuous fruity notes, facing clear, though never too aggressive, sour and citric

name: Pruss Perdu
description: Ale brewed with pears and matured in oak barrels.

name: IPA
description: Modern American IPA, with fruity and pungent aroma and light body.

name: Gigantic-Transatlantic IPA
description: An aromatic and fruity IPA, hopped with Mandarina Bavaria, Cascade, Citra and Mosaic. A collaboration brew made togheter with Gigantic Brewing from Portland.

name: Honey Ma Gold 甫子啤酒
The Wall Builder Imperial Stout 班军乌啤
description:
The first beer to come out of our Great Wall Barrel Program, The Wall Builder is a robust Imperial Stout that we aged in scotch barrels for 4 months. The result is a complex beer with roasted and chocolate character, in combination with myriad of flavors picked up from the barrels.

作为长城桶藏计划的第一款啤酒，班军乌啤是一款口味浓郁的烈性乌啤。在苏格兰威士忌橡木桶中陈酿了4个月后，成酒富含烘焙麦芽与巧克力的口味，与橡木桶赋予其的各种风味浑然一体。

name: Little General IPA 少帅IPA
description:
The Little General IPA is our Chinese-style IPA. Hoppy, but not irresponsibly so, the Little General is a balanced, full bodied IPA made with indigenous, whole flower Chinese hops. Named after the only Patriotic hero to be recognized by both Mainland China and Taiwan, the Little General is an act of balanced beauty.

少帥IPA是大躍獨有的中國風IPA啤酒。酒花香味豐富，口感均衡而非一味苦澀，酒體飽滿，它的釀造全部使用中國產啤酒花，它得名於中國大陸和臺灣唯一公認的愛國將領張學良。少帥IPA想要表達的是一種中庸之美的藝術。

name: Silver Needle White Ale 银针白啤
description:
The Silver Needle White Ale is our summer staple beer. Our lightest beer in color, it is infused with Silver Needle white tea which is known for its light and floral flavor. When consumed as a tea, Silver Needle is usually blended with other teas and flowers to increase its palate presence, but when used in our white ale, the tea brings a subtle and balanced hint of flowers. 

銀針白啤是大躍啤酒夏季的主打酒款。這款啤酒中註入了銀針白茶，並因其色澤和香氣而得名，顏色亦是我們所有酒款中最淺的一款。當人們品嘗銀針白茶時，通常搭配花茶共同飲用從而增強其香氣。而當我們將它釀製成銀針白啤後，這種茶卻為酒體貢獻出一種淡雅又隱秘的花香。

name: Beer Geek Vanilla Shake
description: With 13% alcohol this Imperial Stout pours black with a thick fluffy tan head. Aromas are sweet filled with vanilla. Palate starts with milky sweetness and offers roasted malts, chocolate and coffee.

name: George!
description: Ever been punched in the face by a beer? Our pal George offers anyone willing to try, a thick and oily fist right to the nose. His balance skills are off the charts, but we went ahead and soaked him in bourbon barrels, just to shake things up even more. Good for as many rounds as you can muster up to.

name: Beer Geek Cocoa Shake
description: This dark brown to black beer is packed with aromas of chocolate cake, cocoa, coffee, some butter and dried fruits. Flavor is sweet-based with notes of roasted malt, dark chocolate, lightly bitter coffee, and a savory touch. Full bodied with soft carbonation.

name: Lille Røde
description: Barrel aged sour with raspberries and chokeberries

name: Avalon - FARMER'S RESERVE
description: Single hop, single malt and single variety plum. Primary fermentation in steel, and secondary with wild yeast in Sangiovese barrels on Avalon plums.

name: Stikkelsbær - FARMER'S RESERVE
description: Barrel aged sour with green gooseberries

name: RedFeet - FRIENDSHIP SERIES
description: Four way collaboration with Ale Apothecary, Crooked Stave and Breakside Brewery. We filled our open-top barrels half full with cherries straight off the trees. Then we jumped. American and Norweigen feet turned red and we blended the cherry mash with gently salted wort and wild yeast from each of the four breweries. Secondary fermentation in old red wine barrels, tertiary fermentation in oak vats with 40℅ cherry added.

name: Beat the Landlord Barley Wine 苦大仇深
description:
Brewed only once every 100 batches, this 100% barley malt beer exceeds 10% ABV, yielding a warming and complex barley wine with flavor and aroma meant to be enjoyed at the same pace and attention as a glass of wine.

2015 Asia International Beer Cup Gold Medal Winner.

這是一款百里挑一的啤酒，苦大仇深使用了100%純大麥麥芽所釀造，酒精濃度經超過10%。稱之為Barley Wine是一種簡單的解釋，這款大麥啤酒酒精度、口感和醉人的香氣絕對需要你像品嘗一杯紅酒一樣去慢慢回味。

name: Xenium
description:
Hops: Mosaic & Galaxy
Malt: Pilsner, Oat & Carapils
Yeast: WLP066

name: Nascent
description:
Hops: Amarillo, Simcoe & Enigma
Malt: Pilsner, Oat, Wheat & Carapils
Yeast: WLP066

name: Pretty Good Regards
description: Double mashed imperial stout with toasted coconut and pistachio; no sugar added. Brewed in collaboration with Lervig.

name: Giant Guerrilla
description:
Guerrilla e Giant Step uniscono le loro forze in una DDH DIPA (8,5% vol.) eccezionalmente luppolata, profumata e cremosa senza essere ruvida al palato.
// Guerrilla and Giant Step joine forces in a DDH DIPA (8.5% vol.) Exceptionally hoppy, fragrant and creamy without any rough edge.

name: BR02 / CANTINA
description: English Barley Wine invecchiato per 18 mesi in botti di Rum Caroni.

name: The Boss
description: This specific IPA is a definite house favorite at the BRUS brewery. Now, for the first time ever, it’s in a can! The Boss is a 6.8% DDH IPA with Citra, Amarillo, and Simcoe, and it’s packed to the brim with flavor.

name: Sassy Sauce
description: For this beer, our friends from Cigar City came to Copenhagen to brew this elegant saison. Sassy Sauce is brewed with pilsner, oats and wheat in classic saison style, and fermented with a Belgian saison yeast. We incorporated some slightly newer techniques, where we used Citra in a low temperature whirlpool and then Hallertau Blanc in the dry-hop. This saison is dry and easy to drink, but surprisingly complex, with notes of white wine from the dry-hop and lovely fruity aromas from the Belgian yeast.

name: The Beaning of Life
description: Session pastry stout with cocoa, coffee, almond, and vanilla

name: Good Company
description: Good Company is part of our series to bring you the best of the West coast and the East coast. This beer features the bitterness and drinkability of a west coast, while having the mouthfeel and intense hop aroma of an east coast. Hot side sees Citra and Amarillo in the whirlpool, and we used Simcoe in the dry-hop. Best enjoyed in Good Company.

name: Letra F
description: LETRA F is brewed according to a recipe from the 18th century, with the addition of high amounts of hops to avoid spoilage during the long sea travels from England to India. This IPA has the addition of high amounts of American hops, during its several brewing steps, resulting in hoppy and citric aromas and flavours.

name: Letra F
description: LETRA F is brewed according to a recipe from the 18th century, with the addition of high amounts of hops to avoid spoilage during the long sea travels from England to India. This IPA has the addition of high amounts of American hops, during its several brewing steps, resulting in hoppy and citric aromas and flavours.

name: Raspberry & Lemon Thyme
description: Fruited sour with addition of Thyme.

name: Helles Lager
description:
This multi award winning Helles Lager is brewed with Lager & Sucrose malts and the noble Saaz hop. Herbal, lemon and fresh grain aromas which is light and crisp with an elegantly brisk and dry finish is as close to a traditional Helles as possible.
Originally brewed at 4.5%, now reduced to 4.3%

name: Imparable
description: West Coast-Style IPA made in the Basque Country. Golden color. Loads of fruity hops.

name: Jamberry
description: Jamberry is a hazy IPA brewed with strawberries and black currants. Double dry hopped with Chinook and Slovenian-grown Styrian Dragon, this juicy and full-bodied beer drinks like a mixed-berry smoothie with a lingering pithy finish. Keep cold and drink fresh!

name: We've Been Out There In Orbit
Triple Citra Daydream
description: Triple Citra Daydream! You know the drill: oats, lactose and triple dry hopped with Citra and Citra Lupulin powder.

name: Double Mmm...Fruit Dream (Dragonfruit/Passionfruit/Vanilla/Coconut)
description: Brewed with lactose, conditioned on large amounts of Dragonfruit, Passionfruit, Vanilla and Coconut.

name: HDHC All Green Everything
description: The classic gets the High Density Hop Charge treatment. More hops than you can handle. Flush with Citra, Mosaic, Motueka and Amarillo.

name: Triple Space Diamonds
description: Now Even More Diamonds!!! More Galaxy and more of everything else.

name: Tumbleweeds
description: A new Helles Lager that’s a follow up to our Crickets series. This lager is hopped lightly with Saphir, it’s crispy.

name: Double Dry Hopped Double Mosaic Daydream
Coastal Gose (2018)
description: Few places embody the wild spirit of the Pacific Northwest like the Oregon Coast. To help protect this venerated landscape, we’ve partnered with the Portland Chapter of the Surfrider Foundation on our Coastal Gose blend. This interpretation of the historic Gose beer features sour wheat ales aged in oak barrels with ground coriander seed and sea salt harvested from Oregon’s coastal waters. By donating a portion of the profits from each bottle sold, we are committed to helping the Portland Surfrider Chapter p

name: One Way Or Another
description: Iconic bottles, distinctive flavors and outright admiration for each other. One way or another, we were going to brew a beer with our friends at Cascade Brewing. Together, we developed a new sour tripel recipe that we would brew at our separate facilities with each other - one here in Orange County, CA and the other in Portland, Oregon. The collaborative concept called for treating our creations with the same regional ingredients: Meyer lemons from California and marionberries from Oregon. Both brews would

name: Coral Horizon
description: Coral Horizon is a blend of sour blond ales aged in oak wine barrels for up to 16 months with late infusions of grapefruit zest, hibiscus tea and freshly chopped ginger root. Pouring a brilliant coral-red hue reminiscent of a summer sunset, this small batch blend offers a soft, approachable acidity level with aromas of ruby red grapefruit and a refreshing ginger spice.

name: Manhattan NW
description: Manhattan NW is a blend of sour quad and blond ales aged in bourbon barrels with sour pie cherries and apricot noyaux. A tribute to the classic Manhattan cocktail, this fan favorite features flavors of bourbon, maraschino cherries, bitter almond and a hint of malt sweetness.

name: The Rainbow Project
description: The Rainbow Project is a blend of sour wheat and blond ales aged in oak wine barrels for up to 18 months with orange, lime and lemon zest as well as whole Northwest-grown strawberries. Offering a colorful combination of fruit varieties, this seasonal draft-only release delivers a brilliant polychromatic spectrum of citrus and berry flavor.

name: Valley Flora
description: Barrel aged red ale with pinot noir grapes

name: Garden Party (2017)
description: Garden Party is a blend of sour blond and wheat ales aged in white wine barrels for up to two years with Willamette Valley-grown chardonnay grapes followed by a late infusion of fresh Meyer lemon zest and dried elderflowers. The perfect beverage for any outdoor soirée, Garden Party delivers the sparkle of champagne, the floral delicacy of elderflowers and the brilliance of sweet lemon zest—bringing refinement and refreshment to your party, wherever it may be.

name: Manhattan NW
description: Manhattan NW is a blend of sour quad and blond ales aged in bourbon barrels with sour pie cherries and apricot noyaux. A tribute to the classic Manhattan cocktail, this fan favorite features flavors of bourbon, maraschino cherries, bitter almond and a hint of malt sweetness.

description:
Malt: Pilsner, Oat & Carapils
Hops: Cashmere, Citra & Vic Secret
Yeast: WLP066

description:
Hops: Citra, Cashmere, Mosaic & Idaho 7
Malt: Pilsner, Oat, Wheat & Carapils
Yeast: WLP518 Opshaug Kveik

name: Adaptation
description:
Malt: Pilsner, Oat, Carapils & Rolled Oat
Hops: Citra, Mosaic & Galaxy

description:
Guerrilla e Giant Step uniscono le loro forze in una DDH DIPA (8,5% vol.) eccezionalmente luppolata, profumata e cremosa senza essere ruvida al palato.

name: Audio/Visual Lager
description:
Discover new music with Audio/Visual. This collaborative series celebrates the intersection of art, music and beer, featuring a record label, four bands and one visual artist. Every three months, the bands, the record label and the artist will switch, making room for continued discovery of emerging music of all genres. Audio/Visual Lager is super refreshing, making it the ideal beer for concerts, green rooms, backyards or wherever you tune in.

Audio/Visual is brewed with pilsner malt and brown rice and c

name: Why I Love The Moon
description:
Rainbow Project 2019 - Blue.

Blueberry Gose with the addition of hand picked, local, Borage flowers and Oregon sea salt. ⠀

name: Colour Vision
description:
Rainbow Project 2019 collab featuring all 7 UK breweries.

7 colours of the Rainbow, 7 great international collaborations, but the boxes we ordered to ship the beers in had 8 slots.....We therefore all got together to brew a one off 7 way collaboration to celebrate the project.

This beer was brewed to celebrate the spirit of the Rainbow Project. Brewed with a heavy dry hop of Galaxy, Loral, Mosaic and Voss Kveik yeast.

name: 11 Month Single Select Barrel Buffalo Trace Experimental Rye Imperial Stout
description: COLLAB W. BOTTLE LOGIC & 3 SONS

name: Nightmare Fuel Ella Citra Mosaic Pale Ale
description: American Pale Ale with heavy additions of Ella, Citra and Mosaic hops

name: Emmelie Black Cherry Blackberry Almond Sour
description: Sour fruited beer with black cherries, blackberries and almonds added.

name: I Wanna Be Your Dog
description: Collaboration with Brewdog. Whisky barrel aged coffee pecan mud cake stout

name: OMNIPOLLOSCOPE #4 NEVER MIAMI THUNDER LEMON MERINGUE MILKSHAKE RASPBERRY BLACKBERRY DOUBLE ICE CREAM LASSI GOSE
Original Raspberry Meringue Ice Cream Pie
description: Part of Omnipollo/Buxton Original Ice Cream Series that took off in 2014. Brewed with raspberries, vanilla and lactose.

name: Kokopelli
description: It’s time for the next rotation in our hoppy pale ale series, after Ben comes Kokopelli, with Citra and Mosaic hops. The last rays of sunshine.

name: Cherryversary
description:
This anniversary ale, which is brewed in the solera style, is a blend of red wine and bourbon barrel-aged ale with Montmorency Tart Cherries to lend even deeper red fruit tones. Vanilla beans soften and round out the profile of this celebratory ale lending it a warmth and sweetness. Happy Cherryversary. 

2019 HS box Q1 release.

name: Sourrento
description: Sourrento is a sour ale that was inspired by the lemon flavored spirit, Limoncello which hails from the city of Sorrento, Italy. To create this unique, sweetly sour flavor, we aged our sour blonde ale with both lemon zest and fresh vanilla beans. The resulting beer is somewhere between a classic sour ale, a delightful Italian apertif, and a lemon meringue pie.

name: Train to Beersel (2019)
description: Inspired by a trip to Belgium and designed to resemble the character of lambic found in the town of its namesake, Train to Beersel showcases a slightly higher ABV than you’ll find in most other lambics. As such, the body of the beer is more pronounced, adding a certain roundness to the sour notes while elevating the customary level of funk. Additional complexity is derived from extensive aging in once used French Oak Cabernet Sauvignon barrels and once used American Oak Sauvignon Blanc barrels, and by utili

name: Grey Monday (2019)
description: "Grey Monday is a small batch brew, built on the backbone of our infamous Black Tuesday imperial stout. Aged in barrels with ridiculous amounts of hazelnuts, this beer was originally crafted for a molecular gastronomy dinner at a favorite local restaurant. This treament of our already popular stout was an instant hit both among the restaurant diners and our own staff, begging to be brewed again and bottled up.

name: So Happens It's Tuesday Molé
description: Bourbon Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout with Cacao Nibs, Vanilla, Cinnamon, Lactose, and Cayenne Pepper.

name: Sour Tangie
description:
We love our Sour in the Rye. We love Sorrento. We had a bunch of tangerines and vanilla on hand. It was really that simple. A play on the citrus and honey notes of the rye ale and vanilla from aging in oak barrels, Sour Tangie is citrus-forward with that creamy sweet perception that only vanilla can provide. 

2019 HS box Q1 release.

name: Chocolate Rain (2019)
description: Chocolate Rain began as a single cask at our Black Tuesday release party in 2009. Now this beer sings and stands on its own.

name: Pils
description:
Premiumgeschmack mit zartherber Bitternote.
Glanzfein und hellgelb: So kommt unser Pilsner ins Glas – und ist mit seinem feinporigen Schaum schon optisch ein Erlebnis. Aber wir brauen es ja nicht zum Anschauen. Vielleicht mal riechen? Dabei fällt vor allem ein ausgeprägtes Hopfenaroma auf. Das macht die raffiniert abgestimmte Mixtur aus Hallertauer Aromahopfen. Und wie trinkt sichs? Leicht und trocken. Getragen von einer zartherben Bitternote. Zum Ende hin sehr rund und sehr harmonisch.

Hopfen: Hallerta

name: Helles
description:
Kannst nix falsch machen: Des Helle schmeckt immer.
Geradeaus und geradean – unser Helles ist kein Trunk für viele Worte, sondern ein ehrliches, direktes Bier. Doch lieber a weng philosophisch? Aber bittesehr: Obendrauf sahnig, untendrunter goldgelb, innendrin mild, feinwürzig und mit einer leichten Süße. Aber schon auch mit einer gewissen Hopfenblume. Und von einer Malzigkeit im Ausklang, die einem sofort Lust aufs nächste Seidla macht.

Hopfen: Hallertauer Herkules, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh

name: aU Ungespundet Naturtrüb
description: Wer A sagt, muss auch U sagen. Ungespundet, ungefiltert und unverschämt gut. Halt a U, wie es bei uns heißt. Man hat ja schließlich nicht ewig Zeit zum Bestellen. Und was kommt auf den Tisch, wenn man „a U“ ordert? Eine ganz besondere, hefetrübe Bierspezialität mit vollmundig-weichmalzigem Charakter. Angenehm herb und mit wenig Kohlensäure ist es ein Bier, das zur Brotzeit genauso gut passt wie zum entspannten Feierabend. Hat da einer „Kultbier“ gesagt? Naja, uns soll´s recht sein. Ach ja, „ein“ U, kann man

name: Heller Bock
description:
Stark und samtig. Ein Mordsdrumm von einem Bock.
Kenner und Freunde unseres Bocks freuen sich jedes Jahr auf den Oktober – denn da beginnt die Bockbierzeit. Nicht nur die goldgelbe Farbe dieses Bockes lässt dabei nochmal Erinnerungen an den Sommer aufleben, sondern auch sein reiner, edelhopfiger Duft und das angenehme Malzaroma. Das Einzigartige an diesem Bier ist sein ambivalenter Charakter: Einerseits samtig, fast ölig im Trunk, zeichnet es sich andererseits durch schlanke, herbliche Hopfigkeit aus. Ein

description: Have you heard? We’ve got a new brew on tap! Gossip is a citrus New England IPA with bite and at 6% it’s perfect for sharing the juicy details.

name: Sumatera (2019)
description: コラボレーションにあたり、醸造過程で堀口珈琲のコーヒー焙煎豆を使用し、ラガースタイルのコーヒービールに仕上げました。今回使用したコーヒー豆「LCFマンデリン」は、インドネシア・スマトラ島から届いたばかりのフレッシュな生豆を堀口珈琲の横浜ロースタリーで焙煎したものです。良質なマンデリンには若草やヒノキ、マンゴーなど多様な味わいが感じられますが、今回はフレッシュなマンデリンならではなのフルーティーさを活かした焙煎になっています。ローストとブルーイングのプロ同士が互いの強みを掛け合わせて生まれた特別なコーヒービールをお楽しみください。

name: Coedo Alternative Core
description:
Brut IPA brewed with rice-malt.

この度、数量限定シーズナルビール「Alternative Core（オルタナティブ・コア）」を2018年11月7日（水）出荷開始、全国の飲食店様向けに発売させていただきます！

透き通ったゴールドベージュに、ドライな飲み口と強い炭酸、イースト由来のエステルと5種類のホップにより奏でられるフルーティな味わいと幾重にも重なった華やかなアロマが特徴のIPAです。新たなビアスタイルとして注目されているBrut IPAを、日本を感じられるような素材やイメージを付加して醸造すべく、清酒、味噌、醤油などの日本の伝統的な発酵食品の要である麹菌を使用することに辿り着きました。米麹を使用することにより、モルトのデンプンを徹底的に糖化し、ビールに含まれる糖を最大限発酵させた限りなくドライな、Japanese Brut IPAに仕上がりました。

name: Coedo Shikkoku
description: Fermented for an extended period of time, this dark brew boasts a stunning contrast between the glossy black tone of the beer and the smoothness of the modest pale head. This glossy black beer is called "Shikkoku," named after the famed elegant jet-black lacquer work of Japan.

name: West to East IPA
description: Flavored with Sushi Rice and Yuzu. Ballast Point Brewing and Spirits collaborated first with COEDO Brewery on September 14th, 2012. We traveled west to Japan and brewed a San Diego inspired IPA with a local Japanese twist. West to East IPA was brewed with renowned “Aiyama” Sake Rice and fresh Yuzu peel. We used Magnum and Motueka hops in the boil. Galaxy, Nelson Sauvin, Simcoe, Amarillo, and Centennial for dry hopping with White Labs California Ale yeast for fermentation. An inspirational brew for us, COEDO

name: Blazing World
description:
This beer is a blast wave of dankness. It’s hella dank sauce. It’s the stickiest of the icky. It’s… Alright, I’m done. It’s an amber loaded up with a crapload of Nelson hops, which are some of the fruitiest, dankest, most epically aromatic hops that sweet, sweet money can buy.

Despite its amber hue, this is a fairly dry beer, but it still sports a lightly bready malt backbone that lets us pile on the diggity dankness.

Put it in your face.

name: Floating Upside Down
description:
Back in December 2018, we went to Brooklyn and brewed up Koselig Øl - a double rye IPA with Citra/Idaho 7/Mosaic hops. A few weeks ago, we had the Finback guys at our place to brew up another double rye IPA - this time at a smooth 7.4% with Mosaic and cryo Loral hops which are "changing the brewing world" according to an article on the VERY influential kegerator.com. The subtle spiciness from the rye segues into the dank, herbal notes of the hops with a full-bodied, fruity finish.

A luscious mixture of Vanilla, cocoa, maple syrup with a touch of butterscotch and a hint of coconut brings this thing to the final chapter of things we can add to a stout to make people wonder what the

name: Project Barista: Bourbon Turkish
description: The original Turkish brew was inspired by Turkey’s robust coffee and included not only vanilla, orange zest, nutmeg, figs, cacao and muscavado but also 45kg of Thai coffee. Before barrel ageing, we added more nutmeg, summer orange zest and coffee. After 18 months sat in second use barrels we’re adding Ecuadorian Gonzalo Gaona coffee in the form of a rich espresso, brewed by Redemption Roasters, to maintain big coffee flavours. This is a rich, unctuous and hedonistic coffee beer with a lot going on.

name: Escape Artist
description: Not everything always goes to plan. Sometimes you need a last minute recipe that can get you out of trouble. Sometimes you need an Escape Artist! This is a no-nonsense IPA, with a slightly soft mouthfeel accentuating all the tropical notes that Ekuanot, Simcoe and Mosaic have to offer, balanced by subtle bitterness.

name: Marginal Grains
description: Broaden & Build is a brewery from the team behind world-renowned restaurant Amass. Their beers are influenced by food and foraging, combining the creative processes of chefs and brewers. Marginal Grains uses a blend of foraged wild herbs for unique flavour and bitterness, the tropical aromas of American dry-hopping and, untypically for the style, our house Vermont yeast.                      Thanks to Miles Irving (www.forager.org.uk).

name: Suspended In Centennial
description: Centennial is an absolute favourite hop for craft brewers world wide, so it’s no surprise that we’ve brought Suspended in Centennial back for a second outing. This time, with Simcoe and Ekuanot backing it up, the hop provides big aromas of mango and fruit juice. The flavour is full of citrus, resinous hop character and again, lots of mango, with a lemony zing towards the end.

name: Soundwave IPA
description: Welcome to tropical hop heaven. Soundwave is eminently drinkable, full of flavour and subtle with bitterness. Our most famous beer pours with an inviting haze, while big-hitting American hops deliver fruit notes in abundance and a trademark resinous finish.

description: Animal House is a Spiced Ale brewed with our friends at Graft Cidery (Hudson Valley, NY). Inspired by apple cider donuts, this brew was fermented with a bittersweet cider concentrate and flavored with traditional mulling spices, finishing dry and crisp for a festive fall pint. Keep cold and enjoy fresh! Donuts not included.

name: Helles
description:
Kannst nix falsch machen: Des Helle schmeckt immer.
Geradeaus und geradean – unser Helles ist kein Trunk für viele Worte, sondern ein ehrliches, direktes Bier. Doch lieber a weng philosophisch? Aber bittesehr: Obendrauf sahnig, untendrunter goldgelb, innendrin mild, feinwürzig und mit einer leichten Süße. Aber schon auch mit einer gewissen Hopfenblume. Und von einer Malzigkeit im Ausklang, die einem sofort Lust aufs nächste Seidla macht.

Hopfen: Hallertauer Herkules, Hallertauer Mittelfrüh

description:
A super-charged version of our Imperial Porter. Aged in Kentucky bourbon barrels for over a year, this new Collective Project delivers a smooth combination of rich chocolate flavours from our Imperial porter, married with vanilla and warming alcohol from the barrels. Coming in at 11.5% ABV, in 500ml bottles – this one will warm you up this winter, or cellar it for next year!

Beautiful Art tube packaging with a poster print of Kait Cooper’s art.

description: BCL&V. If you think that’s a mouthful, just wait until you take your first sip. The flavour and aroma of dark berries & stone fruit dominate this fruity sour delight, and are backed up by a generous punch of bright lemon and creamy vanilla.

name: Guava Gose
description: Using our core Gose (Prophets & Nomads) as the base, we added the freshest guava puree we could find. The end result is a perfect balance of tart, sweet, and sour. Expect the Pink Himalayan Salt and flowery guava to leave you refreshed and wanting more.

name: Pina Colada Sour
description: Get ready for sunny days and patio beers with our Pina Colada Sour! We made this sour ale with huge amount of toasted coconut added in the Whirlpool and pineapple during fermentation. Lactose was also used during brewing to add to the creamy sweetness to complete this summer delight.

name: Life in the Clouds
description: Fall into the rich embrace of this New England style IPA. Simcoe and Mosaic hops balance each other to make this juicy IPA explosively fruit forward in both taste and aroma while curbing any unbearable sweetness to make an extremely drinkable beer. The huge mouth feel ensures all of your tastebuds are enveloped in a blanket of tropical bliss, paradise in a can.
